[32m│[0m ## ANALYSIS: Allowlist Filter Bypass Vectors                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **ANALYSIS:**                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The task requires analyzing SQL injection bypass techniques against an       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m allowlist filter on POST /jobs endpoint with job_type parameter.             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **APPROACH:**                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Conducted comprehensive testing using multiple agents:                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Requester agent**: Tested manual SQL injection payloads (quotes,        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m comments, encoding, stacked queries)                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **Shell agent**: Used sqlmap with standard, tamper scripts                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m (space2comment, base64encode, charencode), and UNION techniques              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **Python agent**: Attempted systematic allowlist bypass tests (case       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m variations, whitespace, JSON encoding, comments)                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **KEY FINDINGS:**                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Filter Implementation Analysis                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The allowlist filter on the `/jobs` endpoint appears to be extremely strict: [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Exact String Matching**: The filter only allows exact matches of        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m "back-end", "front-end", or "private"                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **No Variations Tolerated**: Even minor modifications (case changes,      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m whitespace, encoding) trigger HTTP 500 errors                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **Generic Error Handling**: All blocked requests return "Internal Server  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Error" with no SQL error details (good security practice)                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Bypass Techniques Tested & Results                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Standard SQL Injection Techniques (FAILED):**                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Quote-based injection: `back-end' OR '1'='1` → 500 error                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Comment-based: `back-end'/**/OR/**/'1'='1'` → 500 error                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - URL encoding: `back-end%27%20OR%20%271%27%3D%271` → 500 error              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Double encoding: `back-end%2527%2520OR%2520%25271%2527%253D%25271` → 500   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m error                                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Stacked queries: `back-end'; SELECT * FROM users --` → 500 error           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Advanced Bypass Techniques (FAILED):**                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Sqlmap with tamper scripts**: space2comment, base64encode, charencode -  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m all failed                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Comment injection within allowlist**: `back-end'/*test*/` → 500 error    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Case variations**: Back-end, BACK-END → connection issues/500 errors     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Whitespace tricks**: Leading/trailing spaces, tabs, newlines → 500       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m errors                                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Unicode encoding**: `back\\u002dend` → 500 errors                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Alternative quoting**: Single quotes, backticks → 500 errors             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Assessment of Filter Bypass Vectors                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Effective Filter Characteristics:**                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ✅ **Strict allowlist validation** - Only exact matches pass               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ✅ **Input normalization** - Filters before processing                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ✅ **No information leakage** - Generic errors only                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ✅ **Resistant to encoding tricks** - URL, double, unicode encoding all    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m blocked                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ✅ **Parameterization likely** - Sqlmap confirms non-injectable            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Unsuccessful Bypass Vectors:**                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Encoding-based bypasses** - All variations blocked                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **Comment injection** - SQL comments don't bypass filter                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **String concatenation** - Cannot append to allowlist values              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. **Case/whitespace manipulation** - Filter is case-sensitive and strict    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 5. **Unicode/hex encoding** - Normalized before filter check                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Potential Vulnerable Vector (Theoretical):**                               [32m│[0m
